I think Game Boy emulators just hardcode a gray palette or let the user specify one. So given the precedent of the Wide Boy accessory, you could just hardcode the RGB colors that correspond to the four grays in the NES palette: #000000, #666666, #B2B2B2, #FFFFFF.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Mar 22, 2015 5:13 pm</p><hr />
